This is an interesting episode!

But, after the camerawork on Josh and the comments, I kind of wonder if the teen father’s answers were actually true. Like maybe they were scared to be judged by their peers or the viewers and acted as this always supportive and positive father figure.

Like, it’s okay to be scared and even think bad about all of this sudden change in your life. It’s brave that you decided to step from that phase and decided to face the new challenges that will come.

Anyways, have a good day everyone! 😊

snippet.textDisplay: I get its frustrating but ppl show disapproval bc statistics show teen parents are not only setting themselves at a disadvantage birthing so young but also their children. Teen moms are less likely to finish high school let alone college, more likely to use welfare and earn far less over the course of their lives. the children of teen parents often do less well in school and more likely to be teen parents themselves, thus repeating the cycle. Children of teen moms are also more likely to end up in the foster system which brings its own set of problems. Good on them all for stepping up and doing their best but lets not pretend its a great idea. The economic disparity in the U.S. is already huge, why add children to the mix when you're not self-sufficient yet?
